        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 1:08PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 107 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ida, or 17 miles southeast of Atlanta, moving north at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lerch, Stamps, Bradley, Gin City, Buckner, Ida, Fouke, Mandeville,
Vivian, Cavett, Ravanna, Hosston, Genoa, Brightstar, Piney Grove,
Kiblah, Gray, McKamie, Bloomburg, and Canfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for
northeastern Texas.</instruction>
